From: Ashish Kumar Singh <ashishkmr472@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 15 May 2026 22:58:54 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 05/10] tests: Add rigorous Kalman controller-fusion test suite
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

19 first-principles test cases (580 assertions) for
t_tracker_kalman_fusion. Synthetic IMU and optical-pose data is
generated from true rigid-body physics — never from the filter's own
measurement model — and the filter is required to recover ground
truth. Covers lifecycle, orientation (stationary/tilted/rotating/
gyro integration), position and velocity tracking, accelerometer
dead-reckoning including a tilted body frame, robustness (residual
rejection, reset recovery, optical-noise smoothing, dropout
re-convergence, optical latency) and numerical stability.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
